EVALUATION LICENSE — web-rag eval-server image
================================================

Copyright (c) 2026 web-rag operator. All rights reserved.

This software is provided to the named Licensee solely for the purpose of
evaluating their own Retrieval-Augmented Generation system against the
operator's reference system. Any other use is prohibited.

PERMITTED USES
--------------
- Pull and run the container image `ghcr.io/<owner>/web-rag-eval` against
  Licensee's own data and queries.
- Submit query results through the `/api/external/*` endpoints exposed by
  the container.
- Export the JSON evaluation report and share it with the operator.

PROHIBITED USES
---------------
- Reverse engineering, decompiling, disassembling, deobfuscating, extracting
  prompts, or otherwise reconstructing the source code of the container.
- Redistribution, sublicensing, or republishing of the container image or
  any extracted artefact.
- Use of the container for production traffic, paid services, or any
  workload unrelated to the evaluation engagement.
- Removal or alteration of authentication, telemetry, or licence checks.

GHCR ACCESS TOKEN
-----------------
Pulling this image requires a personal access token with `read:packages`
scope on `ghcr.io`. The operator will provide one of:

  (a) a short-lived classic PAT pasted below, or
  (b) an out-of-band link to a single-use credential.

Do NOT commit this file with a populated token to any public location.
Treat the token as a shared secret; if it leaks, notify the operator so
the package can be re-scoped.

  GHCR_USERNAME: <github-username-of-licensee>
  GHCR_PAT:      <paste-token-here>

Pull example:
  echo "$GHCR_PAT" | docker login ghcr.io -u "$GHCR_USERNAME" --password-stdin
  docker pull ghcr.io/<owner>/web-rag-eval:latest

TERMINATION
-----------
This licence terminates automatically on the earlier of (i) the end of the
evaluation engagement as agreed in writing, (ii) the operator revoking the
GHCR token, or (iii) any breach of the prohibited-use section above. Upon
termination, the Licensee must `docker rmi` the image and delete any
report data containing operator-supplied queries.

